               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate notBefore="1800" notAfter="1976" evidence="lettering"/>The name of
                        <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12029GabraMa">Gabra Māryām</persName> is
                     mentioned in a few supplications throughout the manuscript following the phrase
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብርከ፡</foreign> ‘your servant’. He was likely the
                     owner of the manuscript. The production of the manuscript, however, was a
                     collaborative work in which several scribes were involved (see <ref target="#handDesc"/>).</origin>
